In short, both discs have many desirable attributes, but Peachtree Road more explicitly prioritizes midrange vocal intimacy, restrained mastering and an organic album focus that aligns with my stated likes and avoids the polished AOR sheen and potential production polish that would risk diluting vocal immediacy.

